letting idx be domain int(8, 9, 11)
letting t1 be domain tuple(int(1..3), int(4, 6, 8))
letting m1 be domain matrix indexed by [int(3..5), int(8, 9, 11)] of bool
find x: tuple(t1, int(10..12), m1)
such that
    x[1] = (2, 6),
    x[2] % 2 = 0,
    forAll i: idx . x[3][3, i],
    x[3][4, 9] != x[3][5, 11]

